Completing the integration gives the net change as \underline{\phantom{XXXXXX}}\text{ feet.}

choice.explanation:
Completing the integration gives the total distance traveled over [1, 3] \text{:}
\begin{align*} \displaystyle \int_1^{3} |64 - 32t)| \, dt & = \displaystyle \int_1^2 (64 - 32t) \, dt + \displaystyle \int_2^3 -(64 - 32t) \, dt \\ & = (64t - 16t^2) {\Large|}_1^{2} + (-64t +16t^2) {\Large|}_2^3 \\ & = \left( 64(2) - 16(2^2) \right) - \left(64(1) - 16(1^2) \right) \\ & \qquad \quad + \left( -64(3) + 16(3^2) \right) - \left(-64(2) + 16(2^2) \right) \\ & = (128 - 64) - (64 - 16) \\ & \qquad \quad + (-192 + 144) - (-128 +64) \\ & = 32 \end{align*}
So the ballâ€™s total distance traveled is 32\text{ feet.}

